SIMPLE: crotonic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crotonic
<hw>Cro*ton"ic</hw> <pr>(kr?-t?n"?k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to, or derived from, a plant of the genus <gen>Croton</gen>,
or from croton oil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Crotonic acid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>a white
crystalline organic acid, <chform>C3H5.CO2H</chform>, of the ethylene,
or acrylic acid series. It was so named because formerly supposed to
exist in croton oil. Also, any acid metameric with crotonic acid
proper.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The acid characteristic of croton oil is
<xex>tiglic</xex> or <xex>tiglinic acid</xex>, a derivative of
<cref>crotonic acid</cref>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crotonine</ent>⟦br⟧
